1. Hosting ($100–200/mo original → $0–20/mo optimized)
Praxis uses React/TS frontend + Node/Express backend. Focus on free tiers or low-cost PaaS (Platform-as-a-Service) to avoid VPS management overhead.

Use free tiers for MVP:
Frontend (React): Vercel free tier (100GB bandwidth/mo, auto-scaling, no cold starts) or Netlify free (100GB bandwidth/mo, CDN) — handles 10K MAUs easily for static-ish apps like yours. No cost until overages (rare for small traffic).
Backend (Node/Express): Render free tier (100GB bandwidth/mo, always-on for hobby) or Fly.io free credits ($5/mo equivalent, no cold starts). If self-hosting, DigitalOcean $5/mo VPS (1GB RAM, SSD) for full control.

Optimization tips:
Split frontend/backend: Host frontend on free static platforms (Vercel/Netlify), backend on low-cost serverless (Render $7/mo Starter for unlimited requests).
Use Supabase Edge Functions (serverless) instead of full Node backend for API calls — free in Supabase tier, no separate hosting needed.
Monitor usage: Tools like Vercel Analytics (free) to spot bandwidth hogs; compress images/assets to reduce transfer.

New estimate: $0/mo (free tiers for <10K MAU) → $5–10/mo scaled (e.g., Render Starter + Vercel Hobby).

2. Domain Name ($1–$2/mo original → $0/mo optimized)

Free alternatives:
Use subdomains: Vercel.app, Render.com, or GitHub Pages (yourapp.github.io) — fully functional for MVP, no cost.
Free ccTLDs: .tk, .ml, .ga from Freenom (still available in 2026, 12-month renewal, commercial use OK but risky for stability).
Bundled free: IONOS or Bluehost offers free .com/.net for first year with hosting/email plans (if you pay $1–5/mo for basic hosting, domain stays free lifetime with renewal). GitHub Student Pack gives free .com from Namecheap for students/startups.

Optimization tips: Start with subdomain/free ccTLD, upgrade to custom $10/year .com only when branding matters (e.g., post-beta).
New estimate: $0/mo (subdomain or free ccTLD) → $1/mo if bundled.

3. Supabase ($50–$100/mo original → $0–25/mo optimized)
Supabase is usage-based (free tier: 500MB DB, 50K MAU, 1GB storage, no cold starts).

Stick with free tier for MVP: Handles 10K MAUs easily (500MB DB, 1GB storage, unlimited API calls). Pause after 1 week inactivity (no cost when idle).
Optimization tips:
Query optimization: Use indexes, limit rows returned, batch inserts to avoid overages.
Egress minimization: Compress data, cache responses client-side (e.g., React Query).
Free add-ons: Use built-in auth/realtime/edge functions — no extra cost.
Downgrade if needed: Pro $25/mo only for >8GB DB or SOC2 (skip for MVP).

Alternatives for savings:
Firebase free tier (1GB storage, 10GB transfer/mo, Firestore for realtime) — similar to Supabase, mobile-first.
PocketBase/Appwrite self-host free (on $5/mo VPS) — open-source, no usage fees, but manage hosting.
Nhost/Convex free tiers (similar to Supabase, with GraphQL focus).

New estimate: $0/mo (free tier for <50K MAU) → $25/mo if upgrading to Pro.

4. Gemini API ($50–$200/mo original → $0–50/mo optimized)
Token-based (Flash $0.075–0.5/1M input, Pro $1.25–2/1M; free tier 5–15 RPM, 250K tokens/min).

Use free tier for dev: 1,000 requests/day, 250K tokens/min — sufficient for prototyping embeddings/coaching.
Optimization tips:
Context caching: 75–90% savings on repeated prompts (e.g., system messages, user bios) — $0.2–0.4/1M cached vs $2–4 regular.
Prompt engineering: Shorten prompts (reduce tokens 20–50%) — use dynamic templates, trim bios/goals.
Batch processing: 50% discount on non-urgent jobs (e.g., nightly embeddings).
Cheaper models: Use Flash ($0.075–0.5/1M) for embeddings instead of Pro ($1.25–2).
Local caching: Store embeddings in Supabase/DB — reuse for repeat queries (90–98% savings).
Rate limits/budgets: Enforce per-user limits to prevent spikes.

Alternatives: HuggingFace free embeddings (open-source models), or self-host on cheap VPS ($5/mo) with Sentence Transformers — zero API cost after setup.
New estimate: $0/mo (free tier + caching for <10K MAU) → $20–50/mo scaled (Flash + optimizations).

