1. Hosting ($0–20/mo optimized → Potential for $0/mo sustained)
Your current setup leverages free tiers effectively for an MVP with low traffic, but to push further toward zero ongoing costs even as you scale modestly (e.g., up to 50K MAU), focus on serverless architectures and open-source tools that eliminate hosting entirely or shift to community-supported options.
Further optimization tips:

Go fully serverless: Migrate the Node/Express backend to Vercel Serverless Functions or Netlify Functions (both free for 100K invocations/mo). This integrates seamlessly with your React frontend on the same platform, avoiding separate backend hosting. For API-heavy workloads, use Supabase Edge Functions (already mentioned) or AWS Lambda free tier (2M requests/mo, 1M GB-seconds compute) via SST framework for TypeScript support—no cold starts with provisioned concurrency.
Self-host on free hardware: If you have access to old hardware or a Raspberry Pi, run everything via Docker on a home server with dynamic DNS (e.g., DuckDNS free). Power costs are negligible (~$1-2/mo electricity), and use Cloudflare Tunnel (free) for secure public access without port forwarding. This works for non-critical MVPs and avoids all cloud fees.
Hybrid free scaling: Combine GitHub Actions (2,000 minutes/mo free) for backend cron jobs or batch processing, offloading from always-on servers. For traffic spikes, enable auto-scaling on Fly.io's free tier and monitor with their built-in metrics to stay under credits.
Community incentives: Apply for AWS Activate or Google Cloud Startup credits (up to $100K free for eligible startups in 2026), covering any overages for 1-2 years. Similarly, Vercel's Startup Program offers $1K credits.

New estimate: $0/mo (fully serverless or self-hosted for <50K MAU) → $5/mo if needing premium features like custom domains on serverless.
