3. Supabase ($0–25/mo optimized → $0/mo with alternatives or deeper tweaks)
The free tier is generous, but for sustained zero-cost at higher usage, refine data handling or migrate to fully free/self-hosted equivalents while maintaining features like auth and realtime.
Further optimization tips:

Advanced query tuning: Implement Supabase's built-in row-level security and partial indexes to reduce compute usage by 30-50%. Use client-side libraries like TanStack Query for infinite scrolling with pagination, fetching only visible data. For storage, enable auto-compression and deduplication in Supabase settings to stay under 1GB free limit longer.
Feature offloading: Move realtime features to Pusher's free tier (10K messages/day, 100 connections) or Socket.io self-hosted on your free backend tier, freeing Supabase for pure DB/storage.
Full alternatives: Switch to SurrealDB (open-source, self-host on $0/mo via Fly.io free or local Docker)—supports realtime, auth, and GraphQL with no usage limits. Or, use PlanetScale's free tier (MySQL-compatible, 5GB storage, unlimited queries) for the DB portion, integrating with Supabase's auth via API.
Usage forecasting: Integrate free tools like OpenTelemetry to export metrics to Prometheus (self-hosted free), predicting overages and auto-throttling queries dynamically in code.

New estimate: $0/mo (optimized free tier or self-hosted alt for <100K MAU) → $10/mo if scaling requires paid realtime.
4. Gemini API ($0–50/mo optimized → $0–20/mo with open-source shifts)
Your token optimizations are strong; build on them by hybridizing with free/local AI models to handle 80-90% of workloads without API calls.
Further optimization tips:

Deeper caching/hybrid: Use Redis (free tier on Upstash: 10K commands/day) to cache not just contexts but full response embeddings, reducing Gemini calls by another 40%. For non-sensitive tasks, fallback to open-source models like Phi-3 (via HuggingFace free inference API: 1K requests/day) or run locally with Ollama on a $5/mo VPS—zero per-query cost.
Prompt chaining: Break complex prompts into micro-tasks (e.g., summarize bio first with cheap Flash, then coach with cached Pro), saving 20-30% tokens. Implement rate-limiting with exponential backoff in code to spread usage evenly.
User-side computation: Offload lightweight embeddings to client-side JS libraries like Transformers.js (runs in browser, no server cost)—ideal for real-time coaching previews.
Grants and alts: Apply for Google's AI Startup Program (2026 edition offers $350K credits). Alternatives include Anthropic's Claude Haiku (cheaper at $0.25/1M tokens, free tier 5K messages/day) or self-host Grok-like models via xAI's open-source releases on Replicate's free community tier.

New estimate: $0/mo (hybrid local/open-source for core tasks) → $10–20/mo (Gemini for premium features at scale).
